Date Posted: 2014/04/30 16:03:39Ref. JB1001843300
Aviation LawyerGeneral Civil Aviation Authority
UAE General Civil Aviation Authority is pleased to invite applications from qualified Lawyers to join their legal team.
The incumbent will be responsible for:
• Interpreting various legislations,
agreements and obligations under
International conventions,
treaties and agreements
• Prepare and promulgate circulars to airlines and other stakeholders
on regulatory matters
• Review all contracts and MOUs as and when required.
• Provide advice on all legal matters related to aviation
Skills
Education and Qualifications:
A Post Graduate Degree - preferably in International Aviation Law
5 years of experience with at least 2 years in an aviation-field
